sec.p:
The reference genome index was created using BWA v0.7.12 (Burrows Wheeler Aligner), and clean reads were aligned to the reference genome using BWA mem v0.7.12. All peak calling was performed using MACS2. For peak calling simulations per input read, aligned and deduplicated BAM files were used without additional filtering. A peak annotator was used to identify the nearest TSS of each peak, and the distance distribution between peaks and TSS is shown. In addition, the distribution of peak summits on different functional regions, such as the 5’ UTR, CDS, and 3’UTR, was determined. Peak-related genes were confirmed by Peak Annotator, and then GO enrichment analysis was performed to identify the functional enrichment results. Visualisation of custom sequencing data together with conservation data was obtained using the UCSC Genome Browser (
https://genome-asia.ucsc.edu/
).
